<br />
<br />
<br />Hello.  I'm pretty new myself.  Recommend you start reading the docs 
<br />under the NES section on <a href="http://nesdev.com" class="postlink">http://nesdev.com</a>.  I also 
<br />recommend you taking a stab @ 6502 Assembly.  There are lots of docs 
<br />on the net on how to learn 6502.  All the original nintendo games (as far 
<br />as I know) were written in 6502 ASM.  I've never done anything with NES
<br /> dev and C++ or java.  Not sure if you can even do much with those and
<br /> the old NES.  I know they have compilers for basic but I've heard trying 
<br />to do it with basic or C doesn't produce results like 6502 does.  Like I 
<br />said, I'm no expert by far.
<br />
<br />Good Luck.

		

